The evidence with the title 'Money-supply growth hits 36-month high | mises wire ' says Sep 13, 2016  ... Since 2014, money supply growth has ranged from about 7 percent to 8.5 percent. In october of last year, money supply growth hit a seven-year low of 6.8 percent, although this proved not to be an indication of any new trend. Overall, money supply growth has been quite stable over the past two years. 
